Explanation:

The solution iterates through the characters of the first string (word1) and checks if the substring of the second string (word2) starting from the beginning and having the same length as the current character in word1 is equal to the current character in word1. If it is, the count is incremented. This solution has a linear time complexity (O(n)) and constant space complexity (O(1)), making it efficient for solving the problem.

